x4freetext: -THE INTERACTIONS OF NEUTRONS WITH LI-6 AND LI-7
PROTON BOMBARDMENT OF A TRITIUM GAS TARGET,
PULSED BEAM BOMBARDMENT OF DEUTERIUM GAS
.CYLINDRICAL FORM,OF CANNED LITHIUM METAL IN LIGHT
ALUMINIUM CONTAINERS. SAMPLES WERE MADE OF NATURAL
LITHIUM AND LITHIUM ENRICHED TO 95.2 PERCENT LI-6.
THE CHEMICAL PURITY WAS GREATER THAN 98 PERCENT, WITH
MEASURED AT 45 DEGREES FROM HYDROGEN IN POLYTHENE
SAMPLES AT EACH INCIDENT ENERGY. VALUES TAKEN FROM
INTEGRAL DATA RECOMPILED FROM TABLES IN NP,47,385.
.CORRECTION WERE MADE FOR THE TAIL OF THE ELASTIC PEAK
FLUX ATTENUETION, MULTIPLE SCATTERING AND LOW ENERGY
NEUTRON EMISSION. CORRECTIONS FOR THE PRESENCE OF TWO
ISOTOPES IN THE SAMPLES HAVE BEEN MADE TO THE 2.18MEV
INELASTIC DATA OF LI-6, AND THE 0.48 AND 4.63 MEV DAT
OF LI-7, WITH THE REMAINING CROSS SECTIONS CALCULATED
PER ATOM OF LI IN THE SAMPLES.
.QUOTED ERRORS ARE AT ONE STANDARD DEVIATION AND
REPRESENT STATISTICAL ERRORS AND A CONTRIBUTION FROM
